.TH SING\-GATEWAY 1 "May 2026" "sing\-gateway 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sing\-gateway \- manage sing\-box TProxy gateway integration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sing\-gateway
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sing\-gateway
is a companion command for sing\-box gateway deployments. It discovers the local
sing\-box configuration, validates gateway settings, and applies or removes the
optional TProxy gateway integration.
.
.PP
Installation is inert by default. Gateway state is changed only when an explicit
command such as
.B enable
or
.B set
is run.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B check
Validate and print the resolved gateway configuration.
.TP
.B print\-command
Print the delegated
.B tproxy_ctrl.sh set
command without applying it.
.TP
.B print\-nft
Print generated nftables rules through
.B tproxy_ctrl.sh \-\-dry\-run.
.TP
.B set
Apply the resolved gateway state through
.BR tproxy_ctrl.sh .
.TP
.B unset
Clean managed gateway state through
.BR tproxy_ctrl.sh .
.TP
.B enable [\-\-force]
Install the sing\-box.service drop\-in and reload systemd.
.TP
.B disable
Remove the sing\-box.service drop\-in, perform best\-effort cleanup, and reload
systemd.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SING_GATEWAY_CONFIG
Path to the gateway configuration file. Defaults to
.IR /etc/sing\-gateway/gateway.conf .
.TP
.B SING_GATEWAY_CTRL
Path to the delegated TProxy control script.
.TP
.B SING_GATEWAY_SERVICE
Name of the managed sing\-box systemd service. Defaults to
.IR sing\-box.service .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/sing\-gateway/gateway.conf
Gateway configuration file.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/sing\-gateway/tproxy_ctrl.sh
Delegated TProxy control script.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sing\-box (8),
.BR systemctl (1),
.BR nft (8)
